  <title>CI</title>

  <section>
    <title>GitHub CI</title>

    <section>
      <title>Self Hosting CI</title>

      <para>
        A self-hosted CI
        <indexterm>
          <primary>CI</primary>
          <secondary>GitHub</secondary>
        </indexterm>
        runner is assigned to a single project.
      </para>

      <para>
        <link
            xlink:href="https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/26893#discussioncomment-3253827"
        >
          Configuring the runner without any prompting.
        </link>

        <screen>./config.sh --url $repo_url --token $PAT --agent $runner_name --work $work_dir --runasservice</screen>
      </para>

      <para>
        GitHub prefers ephemeral runners.
      </para>

      <para>
        You can run a single runner for multiple projects.
        <link
            xlink:href="https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/26258#discussioncomment-3251019"
        >
          Registering Multiple Runners On One Host
        </link>
      </para>

    </section>

  </section>

